25/05/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Representatives of governments and companies from the three countries involved in the Bourgas-Alexandroupolis oil pipeline project -- Bulgaria, Greece and Russia -- visited the construction site on Greek territory Tuesday (24 May) to inspect preparations. 
A trilateral protocol on co-operation was signed on 12 April, paving the way for the start of work on the project. 
The delegations are expected to visit the Bulgarian site in Bourgas by the end of this week. 
A two-day meeting of the trilateral committee for the pipeline and corporate participants begins Thursday in Sofia. 
(Kathimerini - 25/05/05; MPA - 24/05/05)
